Once again, we are in the throes of industrial action in the health sector. The nurses and clinical officers declared strikes starting this past week, and the doctors suspended theirs for two more weeks to allow for consultations.
Since the registration of the doctors’ union, December strikes have become almost de rigueur. Unfortunately, there is also little variation in the grievances leading up to the strikes, and perhaps it is time we spent a little time interrogating the reasons behind the frequent strikes.



