A perennial complaint is that an aspect or other of remuneration has been neglected or ignored, and the workers are going on strike to enforce an old agreement on remuneration or salary increment. Industrial relations practice does not anticipate that a reality can exist in which an employer enters an agreement with an employee and fails to keep their end of the bargain.



