Indeed, industrial harmony is only maintained on the premise that each party in the tripartite arrangement will keep their end of the bargain, and that courts exist to enforce the rights of any of the parties that might feel wronged.
Unfortunately, as we continue to wallow in the confusion inherent in our constitutional transition and our experiment with democratic governance, we are encountering instances where employers are entering agreements they either have no capacity to implement, or employees are pushing for agreements they know will not be implemented.
Collective bargaining agreements
The end result is that negotiated collective bargaining agreements are not being implemented, and the industrial relations environment is becoming ever more toxic.
It is my opinion that we need a huge dose of honesty in our industrial relations environment. In order to achieve this, it is important for public sector employers to confront the reality that things changed in 2010.



